I'm gonna grab my things and I'm gonna walk out of here.

187
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:20,840
- 好吧 - 好了 兄弟？
-All right. -All right, brother?

188
00:31:20,910 --> 00:31:22,240
是
Yeah.

189
00:31:23,010 --> 00:31:24,270
是

190
00:32:02,250 --> 00:32:06,340
大地因你而受诅
"Cursed be the ground for our sake.

191
00:32:08,160 --> 00:32:13,490
荆棘与疾黍将在我们面前出现
"Both thorns and thistles it shall bring forth for us.

192
00:32:15,760 --> 00:32:19,640
我们从地中来 我们从尘土中来
"For out of the ground, we were taken. For the dust, we are.

193
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:24,660
“也必将归于尘土”
"And to the dust, we shall return."

194
00:32:53,430 --> 00:32:54,930
住手！
Stop!

195
00:32:57,430 --> 00:32:58,760
求你了
Please.

196
00:33:10,050 --> 00:33:11,540
瑞德利治
Redridge!

197
00:33:12,280 --> 00:33:13,570
瑞德利治
Redridge.

198
00:33:27,700 --> 00:33:29,400
你是谁？
And who are you?

199
00:33:30,460 --> 00:33:31,670
无名鼠辈
Nobody.

200
00:33:33,170 --> 00:33:35,420
我不信
I doubt that.

201
00:33:35,510 --> 00:33:39,470
在我的酒吧里被杀的那些人 他们才是无名鼠辈
The men you killed in my bar, now, they were nobody.

202
00:33:40,750 --> 00:33:43,150
- 但是你 - 他的手没有抖
-But you, now. -He ain't got the shakes.

203
00:33:43,220 --> 00:33:45,680
- 他不是他们一伙的 - 很好
-He ain't one of them. -Good.

204
00:33:46,480 --> 00:33:50,270
这是一个文明的城市 我们不吃人
This is a civilized town. We don't eat humans.

205
00:33:51,650 --> 00:33:55,280
我们这儿不常见到很多从前的人 现在不常见了
We don't see too many people from before. Not anymore.

206
00:33:57,320 --> 00:33:59,990
- 你看书吗？ - 每天
-Do you read? -Every day.

207
00:34:00,330 --> 00:34:03,620
好 这对你很好 我也每天看
All right. Well, good for you. Me, too.

208
00:34:04,570 --> 00:34:05,900
你知道吗 真有趣
You know, it's funny.

209
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:10,790
虽然我们都老了 你我这样的人 我们却是未来
As old as we are, people like you and me, we're the future.

210
00:34:11,670 --> 00:34:12,960
你想怎样？
What do you want with me?

211
00:34:13,950 --> 00:34:15,440
直奔主题！
Straight to the point!

212
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:20,260
我喜欢这样！
I like that!

213
00:34:24,890 --> 00:34:26,680
你不仅是受过教育
You're not just educated.

214
00:34:28,190 --> 00:34:30,650
我从没见过谁有这么好的身手
I never saw anyone handle themselves the way you did.

215
00:34:30,730 --> 00:34:35,400
我不知道你从哪儿学来的那些 但是我肯定我用得上你
I don't know where you learned it, but I sure as hell could use it.

216
00:34:35,470 --> 00:34:39,400
这个小城只是一个开始
This little town, just the beginning.

217
00:34:39,470 --> 00:34:41,570
我打算对外扩建
I'm about to expand.

218
00:34:41,640 --> 00:34:43,970
我需要专业人士的帮助 我可以任用你这样的人
I need expert help. I could use someone like you.

219
00:34:44,580 --> 00:34:47,540
谢谢 但我真的不感兴趣
Thank you, but I'm really not interested.

220
00:34:48,210 --> 00:34:50,960
替我干活的人 过得比任何行者做梦梦到的都好
Well, the people who work for me live better than any walker ever dreamed.

221
00:34:51,040 --> 00:34:53,670
问问瑞德利治 问问兄弟们 随便问谁
Ask Redridge here. Ask the boys, anyone.

222
00:34:54,550 --> 00:34:56,800
真正的床 热乎的饭菜 还有女人
Real beds, hot food, women.

223
00:34:59,890 --> 00:35:01,510
干净的水
Clean water.

224
00:35:02,460 --> 00:35:04,730
你去别的地方可能会差很多 伙计
You could do a lot worse, my friend.

225
00:35:06,220 --> 00:35:07,600
谢谢你
Thank you,

226
00:35:09,390 --> 00:35:11,770
但我必须去一个地方
but I got somewhere I need to be.

227
00:35:11,840 --> 00:35:13,140
去哪儿？
Where?

228
00:35:14,270 --> 00:35:15,440
西方
West.

229
00:35:15,980 --> 00:35:17,780
西方什么都没有
There is nothing west.

230
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:19,810
别人告诉我的和你说的不一样
I've been told different.

231
00:35:19,910 --> 00:35:21,200
谁告诉你的？
By who?

232
00:35:26,690 --> 00:35:28,020
告诉你吧
Tell you what.

233
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:33,040
在这儿住一晚 感受一下当地的热情好客 看看自己是否喜欢
Stay the night. Try a little local hospitality, see how you like it.

234
00:35:33,750 --> 00:35:35,540
咱们明早再谈
We'll talk again in the morning.

235
00:35:36,160 --> 00:35:39,150
给你个忠告 行者 这不是选择
Word of advice, Walker. It's not a choice.

236
00:35:41,500 --> 00:35:43,470
永远都是选择
It's always a choice.

237
00:35:47,370 --> 00:35:50,640
整晚都会有人在你的房间外
There'll be someone outside your room all night

238
00:35:50,710 --> 00:35:52,370
要是你有任何需要的话
if you need anything.

239
00:35:52,480 --> 00:35:54,060
我什么都不需要
I don't need anything.

240
00:35:54,710 --> 00:35:56,270
那可说不准
You never know.

241
00:36:47,570 --> 00:36:51,870
这是给你的 一些洗漱用的水和食物
This is for you. It's some water for washing and some food.

242
00:36:52,440 --> 00:36:55,880
还有些许特殊藏品 代表房主的问候
Little special reserve, too, compliments of the house.

243
00:37:00,510 --> 00:37:04,010
你得把这个接过去 或者说句话 这样我才能知道你在哪
I need you to take this or say something so I can find you.

244
00:37:15,900 --> 00:37:19,360
- 谢谢 - 不客气
-Thank you. -You're welcome.

245
00:37:19,430 --> 00:37:22,230
- 你还需要我帮你拿些什么吗？ - 不 不用了 谢谢
-Can I get you anything else? -No, I'm fine. Thank you.

246
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:25,320
你失明是因为战争 还是因为战后的阳光？
Did you get blinded in the war or by the sun after?

247
00:37:27,970 --> 00:37:30,570
我生来如此
I was born this way.

248
00:37:30,640 --> 00:37:33,540
我想或许我是幸运的 因为当一切发生时
I think probably I'm lucky, because I was already used to being like this

249
00:37:33,610 --> 00:37:35,640
我就已经习惯这样了
by the time it happened.

250
00:37:36,320 --> 00:37:38,910
好吧 那么 谢谢你给我送吃的来
Right, well, thank you for the food.

251
00:37:39,540 --> 00:37:41,050
不客气
You're welcome.

252
00:37:43,290 --> 00:37:44,980
我喜欢你的香水
I like your perfume.

253
00:37:49,720 --> 00:37:51,430
只是香波而已
It's just shampoo,

254
00:37:52,560 --> 00:37:54,180
但是谢谢你
but thank you.

255
00:37:56,800 --> 00:37:58,170
晚安
Good night.

256
00:38:22,130 --> 00:38:25,630
我不认为他明早会改变主意
I don't think he's gonna change his mind by the morning.

257
00:38:26,630 --> 00:38:28,510
他不会留下的
He's not gonna stay.

258
00:38:32,930 --> 00:38:35,060
他和其他人不同
He's different than the others.

259
00:38:36,040 --> 00:38:40,100
你没法让他听命于你的
You're not gonna be able to make him do what you want him to do.

260
00:38:41,940 --> 00:38:44,110
谁说是听命于我？
Who said anything about me?

261
00:38:46,490 --> 00:38:48,490
我会派索拉拉去
I'll send Solara.

262
00:38:52,530 --> 00:38:54,490
你不能那么做
You can't do that.

263
00:38:54,560 --> 00:38:57,690
是时候让她派上更大用场了
It's about time I got better use out of her.

264
00:39:00,030 --> 00:39:01,160
不要那么做
Don't.

265
00:39:02,170 --> 00:39:03,420
求你
Please.

266
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:08,570
求你了 不要 求你 求你
Please, don't. Please. Please.

267
00:39:10,640 --> 00:39:11,930
求求你！
Please!

268
00:39:23,860 --> 00:39:25,520
我能进来吗？
Can I come in?

269
00:39:28,060 --> 00:39:29,720
等一分钟
Give me a minute.

270
00:39:38,710 --> 00:39:41,670
已经有人送过食物和水了
Somebody already came with food and water.

271
00:39:44,080 --> 00:39:46,100
需要的我都有了
I got everything I need.

272
00:39:50,380 --> 00:39:52,470
你确定吗？
Are you sure about that?

273
00:39:56,090 --> 00:39:58,390
这儿还真是明亮
It's really bright in here.

274
00:40:00,060 --> 00:40:01,230
我叫索拉拉
I'm Solara.

275
00:40:01,290 --> 00:40:05,060
是 你在楼下给我装的水
Right. You filled my canteen downstairs.

276
00:40:06,100 --> 00:40:08,970
是呀 你是那个行者 不是吗？
Yeah. You're the walker, right?

277
00:40:10,030 --> 00:40:11,240
是
Right.

278
00:40:14,440 --> 00:40:18,380
你要是担心钱的问题 都算在房主账上了
If you're worried about paying, it's on the house.

279
00:40:18,440 --> 00:40:20,070
什么钱？
Paying for what?

280
00:40:22,150 --> 00:40:24,140
你干嘛不坐下来？
Why don't you take a seat?

281
00:40:34,130 --> 00:40:35,250
不
No.

282
00:40:37,260 --> 00:40:41,180
不 我不能走 我不能 我要是走了 他会伤害我妈妈的
No, I can't go. I can't. If I do, he'll hurt my mom.

283
00:40:42,270 --> 00:40:44,190
- 谁？ - 卡耐基
-Who? -Carnegie.

284
00:40:46,310 --> 00:40:47,400
他是你父亲？
He's your father?

285
00:40:48,170 --> 00:40:51,170
不 不是 但我们照样都属于他
No. No, but we belong to him just the same.

286
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:54,530
听着 我可以睡地板
Look, I'll sleep on the floor.

287
00:40:54,680 --> 00:40:56,240
明天你可以告诉他你过得很愉快
Tomorrow you can tell him you had a good time.

288
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:59,080
我保证我不会惹麻烦
I promise you I will be no trouble.

289
00:41:02,910 --> 00:41:04,210
求你了？
Please?

290
00:41:11,030 --> 00:41:14,760
骑士到象四
Knight to bishop four.

291
00:41:22,810 --> 00:41:24,310
该你了
Your move.

292
00:41:31,220 --> 00:41:33,950
那 你多大了？
So, how old are you?

293
00:41:34,890 --> 00:41:36,320
什么？
Excuse me?

294
00:41:36,390 --> 00:41:41,220
因为我很少看到你这个年纪的人上这儿来
It's just that I haven't really seen too many people your age come through here before.

295
00:41:41,330 --> 00:41:43,540
自从文明毁灭
Well, it's been

296
00:41:47,790 --> 00:41:50,210
已经过了３０个冬天了
30 winters since the flash.

297
00:41:53,670 --> 00:41:55,300
我真的不记得了
I really don't remember.

298
00:41:56,580 --> 00:42:00,840
你还记得一切是什么样子的吗？ 我是说 从前的世界
Do you remember what it was like? I mean, in the world before.

299
00:42:00,910 --> 00:42:02,180
我知道
Yeah.

300
00:42:05,850 --> 00:42:07,770
那 从前是什么样子的？
Well, what was it like?

301
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:14,320
人们拥有的比需要的多
People had more than they needed.

302
00:42:16,260 --> 00:42:20,600
我们不知道何为珍贵
We had no idea what was precious, what wasn't.

303
00:42:25,610 --> 00:42:29,340
我们丢弃了很多东西 而现在的人却为了那些东西自相残杀
We threw away things people kill each other for now.

304
00:42:31,610 --> 00:42:33,440
- 真的？ - 真的
-Really? -Yeah.

305
00:42:35,620 --> 00:42:37,080
你有一本书
You have a book.

306
00:42:37,180 --> 00:42:39,300
- 我能看看吗？ - 不能
-Can I see it? -No, you cannot.

307
00:42:39,390 --> 00:42:41,600
- 我只是 只是想看看 - 不行 我说了不行
-I just, I just wanna look at it. -No. I said no.

308
00:42:41,680 --> 00:42:44,310
听着 我根本不识字！ 来吧 求你了 我只是想看看
Listen, I can't even read! Come on, please, let me just see it.

309
00:42:46,390 --> 00:42:48,060
你到底怎么了？不过是本书罢了！
What is with you? lt is just a book!

310
00:42:48,130 --> 00:42:49,890
这不只是一本书
It's not just a book.

311
00:42:50,560 --> 00:42:53,070
- 什么意思？什么叫不只是一本书？ - 听着
-What do you mean, it's not just a book? -Look.

312
00:42:53,130 --> 00:42:57,630
不许再问书的事情了 明白吗？ 不要再问了 好不好？
No more questions about the book, all right? No more questions. All right?

313
00:43:22,720 --> 00:43:25,100
既然你在这儿 我想问你个问题
I got a question for you, since you're here.

314
00:43:25,600 --> 00:43:27,930
我可能回答也可能不回答
Well, maybe I'll answer it and maybe I won't.

315
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:31,730
你从哪儿弄到的水？
Where do you get your water?

316
00:43:32,670 --> 00:43:34,070
不能告诉你
Can't tell you that.

317
00:43:34,140 --> 00:43:37,270
- 是你不能说还是你不知道？ - 哦 我知道的
-You can't tell me or you don't know? -Oh, I know.

318
00:43:38,010 --> 00:43:43,140
但要是你不告诉我书的事情 我就不告诉你水的事情
But if you're not talking about the book, I'm not talking about the water.

319
00:43:46,790 --> 00:43:48,830
知道吗 你这人真滑稽
You're something else, you know.

320
00:43:49,690 --> 00:43:51,620
好吧 我还有个问题
All right, I got another question for you.

321
00:43:51,690 --> 00:43:53,320
说吧
Right.

322
00:43:53,420 --> 00:43:55,630
你饿吗？
You hungry?

323
00:43:55,700 --> 00:43:57,690
这儿有很多吃的
There's a lot of food there,

324
00:43:58,090 --> 00:43:59,840
我一个人吃不掉
more than I can eat.

325
00:44:00,930 --> 00:44:02,380
告诉你吧
Tell you what.

326
00:44:02,470 --> 00:44:06,890
我们可以分享 你知道 就像曾经老人们那样
We can share it, you know, like old people used to.

327
00:44:09,270 --> 00:44:11,020
好吧
Okay.

328
00:44:11,100 --> 00:44:12,230
好？
Okay?

329
00:44:16,850 --> 00:44:19,550
等一分钟 等一分钟 等等 坐下
Wait a minute, wait a minute. Wait. Sit.

330
00:44:21,890 --> 00:44:22,980
坐下
Sit.

331
00:44:24,780 --> 00:44:26,910
这是给你的
This'll be for you.

332
00:44:27,790 --> 00:44:29,080
把手给我
Give me your hands.

333
00:44:31,230 --> 00:44:32,560
你干什么？
What are you doing?

334
00:44:32,900 --> 00:44:34,890
相信我 把手给我
Trust me. Give me your hands.

335
00:44:39,300 --> 00:44:40,920
闭上眼睛
Close your eyes.

336
00:44:42,910 --> 00:44:45,840
亲爱的主 我们感谢您赐予我们面前的食物
Dear Lord, we thank you for this meal.

337
00:44:45,910 --> 00:44:49,370
感谢您赐予我们温暖的床
We thank you for a warm bed

338
00:44:49,470 --> 00:44:53,350
感谢您赐予我们头顶的屋檐 使我们不致受冻
and a roof over our head on cold nights such as this.

339
00:44:54,250 --> 00:44:56,150
太长了
It's been too long.

340
00:44:56,480 --> 00:44:58,070
是你从那本书里看到的？
Is this from your book?

341
00:44:59,090 --> 00:45:01,750
别插嘴 闭上眼睛
Don't interrupt. Close your eyes.

342
00:45:03,700 --> 00:45:08,030
感谢您在这样的艰苦岁月中
We thank you for the gift of companionship

343
00:45:08,100 --> 00:45:10,430
给予我们陪伴
in hard times like these.

344
00:45:11,330 --> 00:45:12,700
阿门
Amen.

345
00:45:17,380 --> 00:45:18,840
现在可以吃了？
Now we eat?

346
00:45:20,080 --> 00:45:21,600
可以吃了
Now we eat.

347
00:45:52,650 --> 00:45:54,140
早上好 索拉拉
Good morning, Solara.

348
00:45:55,870 --> 00:45:58,670
昨晚过得怎样？睡得好吗？
How was your night? Did you sleep well?

349
00:45:58,750 --> 00:46:00,420
我照你说的做了
I did like you said.

350
00:46:00,650 --> 00:46:02,920
你当然要按我说的做
Of course you did what I said.

351
00:46:03,990 --> 00:46:07,320
但是有用吗？他会留下来吗？
But did it work? Is he staying?

352
00:46:08,260 --> 00:46:10,350
我们没怎么说话
We didn't do much talking.

353
00:46:11,260 --> 00:46:13,520
索拉拉 亲爱的 吃点东西
Solara, honey, eat something.

354
00:46:17,100 --> 00:46:19,020
妈妈 把手给我
Mom, give me your hand.

355
00:46:21,670 --> 00:46:23,340
闭上眼睛
Close your eyes.

356
00:46:23,980 --> 00:46:25,500
妈妈 相信我
Mom, trust me.

357
00:46:32,180 --> 00:46:33,450
亲爱的主
Dear Lord.

358
00:46:35,350 --> 00:46:37,450
我们感谢您赐予我们食物
We thank you for our food.

359
00:46:38,790 --> 00:46:40,750
感谢您赐予我母亲
Thank you for my mother.

360
00:46:42,530 --> 00:46:46,430
感谢您赐予我们头顶的屋檐 和新的朋友
Thank you for the roof over our heads and our new friends.

361
00:46:49,200 --> 00:46:50,460
还有
And...

362
00:46:56,210 --> 00:46:58,870
嗯 我想就这么多
Well, I guess that's all for now.

363
00:46:59,550 --> 00:47:00,880
阿门
Amen.

364
00:47:06,940 --> 00:47:09,780
这是你要说的词 阿门
That's the word you're looking for. Amen.

365
00:47:12,190 --> 00:47:13,950
是结束语
That's how you stop.

366
00:47:20,900 --> 00:47:23,160
你还说你们没怎么说话
You said you didn't talk much.

367
00:47:25,240 --> 00:47:27,470
那他看书了吗？
But did he do any reading?

368
00:47:29,740 --> 00:47:32,400
- 我再问你问题 - 比尔 别
-I asked you a question. -Bill, don't.

369
00:47:32,510 --> 00:47:35,100
